The paper deals with the design of precoding vectors in a MIMO interference channel, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses game-theoretic concepts, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.GT (game theory). Additionally, the paper mentions applications such as multi-cell coordination in cellular networks and spectrum sharing in cognitive radio networks, which are topics related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the improvement and reinterpretation of existing techniques, which could fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
